    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/8–3044</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Greek Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Greek Embassy in Moscow has drawn the attention of the Greek Government on
                    the possibility that German forces could be <pb facs="0392" n="380"
                        xml:id="pg_380"/> withdrawn to Greece from Bulgaria, owing to the impending
                    surrender of the latter. The Greek Government strongly feels the necessity that
                    a special clause be included in the armistice with Bulgaria, preventing such an
                    eventuality.</p>
                <p>Information from official Turkish sources indicates that German forces have
                    already evacuated the northern section of the Evros district and that the region
                    in question is under the control of the underground.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-30">August 30,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
